# How to stop creating method with event · pocketbase/pocketbase · Discussion #877
created: 2022-10-31, last updated: 2026-04-18, [Read more](https://github.com/pocketbase/pocketbase/discussions/877)

Returning any non-nil go `error` should stop the create operation.
For example:
```
app.OnRecordBeforeCreateRequest().Add(func(e *core.RecordCreateEvent) error {
eventData := e.Record
return checkFreeSlot(app, eventData)
})...return errors.New("Something went wrong");
// or if you want a formatted json error you could use:
// (PB v0.8.0) return apis.NewBadRequestError("Something went wrong", nil)
// (PB v0.7.9) return rest.NewBadRequestError("Something went wrong", nil)
}
```
...
@Enferum You can just set/overwrite the data in your `e.Record`.
```
// for PocketBase v0.7.x:
e.Record.SetDataValue("yourFieldName", "test123")
// for PocketBase v0.8.0-rc1:
e.Record.Set("yourFieldName", "test123")
```
You don't need to explicitly persist it.
The finalizer of the hook event will make the call to the database for you if there were no errors.

